issue.body:
If the first argument of assertThat is a generic that cannot be inferred, compilation fails with: 

reference to assertThat is ambiguous 
both method assertThat (java.lang.CharSequence) in org.assertj.core.api.Assertions and method <T>assertThat(org.assertj.core.api.AssertProvider<T>) in org.assertj.core.api.Assertions match

The code snippet below demonstrates the error:

``` java
package com.example.assertj;

import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.*;

import org.assertj.core.api.Assertions;
import org.junit.Test;

public class AssertjTest {

    public static <T> T returnGeneric() {
        return (T) new Object();
    }

    @Test
    public void failsToCompileWithJava8(){
        assertThat(returnGeneric()).isEqualTo("foo");
    }
}

```

This was done using assertj-core 3.1.0

Workaround is to explicitly cast. e.g.

``` java
        assertThat((Object) returnGeneric()).isEqualTo("foo");
```

Is this something that can be fixed within assertj, or is there no way to avoid the explicit cast?

#### Summary

Custom assertion for class implementing Comparable causes compilation errors under Java 8. This happens only when Comparable class is parametrized. Tested with assertj-core 3.5.2
#### Example

``` java
public class MyClass<T> implements Comparable<MyClass<T>> {
    @Override
    public int compareTo(MyClass<T> o) {
        return 0;
    }
}
public class MyClassAssert extends AbstractAssert<MyClassAssert, MyClass<?>> {
    public MyClassAssert(MyClass<?> actual) {
        super(actual, MyClassAssert.class);
    }
}
public class MyAssert extends org.assertj.core.api.Assertions {
    public static MyClassAssert assertThat(MyClass<?> myClass) {
        return new MyClassAssert(myClass);
    }
}

import static MyAssert.assertThat;
public class MyClassTest {
    public static void test() {
        assertThat("abc").isEqualTo("abc");
        MyClass<String> myObj = new MyClass<>();
        assertThat(myObj).isEqualTo(myObj);
    }

```

[ERROR] MyClassTest.java:[6,9] reference to assertThat is ambiguous
[ERROR] both method assertThat(MyClass<?>) in MyAssert and method <T>assertThat(T) in org.assertj.core.api.Assertions match
